Sentencas: A solid solution (Ti,W)(3)SiC2 possessing good oxidation resistance and low area-specific resistance (ASR) after oxidation has been synthesized by an in-situ hot pressing process.
Titulo: Exploring a novel ceramic (Ti,W)3SiC2 for interconnect of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The oxidation rate constant at 800 degrees C in air is 6.29 x 10(-14) g(2) cm(-4)
Titulo: Exploring a novel ceramic (Ti,W)3SiC2 for interconnect of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell
Exploring a novel ceramic (Ti,W)3SiC2 for interconnect of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The formed single-layer oxide is composed of W doped ruffle TiO2 and amorphous SiO2.
Titulo: Exploring a novel ceramic (Ti,W)3SiC2 for interconnect of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: SiO2 is evenly inlaid in the communicative body frame of TiO2.
Titulo: Exploring a novel ceramic (Ti,W)3SiC2 for interconnect of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: W doped in TiO2 mainly exists as W. W doping not only hinders the outward diffusion of Ti by decreasing the concentration of native Ti interstitials in TiO2, but also restrains the inward diffusion of oxygen by decreasing the concentration of O vacancies.
Titulo: Exploring a novel ceramic (Ti,W)3SiC2 for interconnect of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Furthermore, W dopant in TiO2 enhances the electrical conductivity of TiO2 by increasing the concentration of semi-free electron.
Titulo: Exploring a novel ceramic (Ti,W)3SiC2 for interconnect of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Therefore, the low ASR of (Ti,W)(3)SiC2 after oxidation owes to high electrical conductivity of TiO2 as well as the reduced thickness of oxide scale.
Titulo: Exploring a novel ceramic (Ti,W)3SiC2 for interconnect of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: All the results render (Ti1-xWx)(3)SiC2 promising as interconnects for the intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Exploring a novel ceramic (Ti,W)3SiC2 for interconnect of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell
